# Function Parameter Style

When a function needs multiple inputs, prefer a single object parameter instead of positional parameters.

Use this especially when:
- the function has 2 or more parameters
- parameters have the same or similar types
- parameters are optional now or may grow later

Single, simple primitive parameters are allowed.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD: positional parameters are easier to mix up
function createUser(name: string, age: number) {
  // ...
}

// ✅ GOOD: named fields are explicit and extensible
function createUser({ name, age }: { name: string; age: number }) {
  // ...
}

// ✅ ALLOWED: simple single-argument function
function getUserById(userId: string) {
  // ...
}
```
